author: Staff
title: Prep Player of the Week: Honorable mention (Oct. 6)
text:
Prep Player of the Week: Honorable mention (Oct. 6) published Tuesday, October 6, 2015 Football Greg Smith, Yusuf Green, Auwan Fleming, Cedar Shoals: Smith had 80 yards and a touchdown on 10 carries in the Jaguars’ 20-3 win over Heritage-Conyers on Friday. Green had seven tackles and two interceptions. Fleming graded out at 90 percent, and led the way for Colbert. Colby Wood, Jefferson: Wood tallied 285 yards and four touchdowns on 45 carries to help Jefferson to a 27-8 win over Elbert County on Friday. He also had an interception. Travis Kellogg, Carson Turner, Cody Lee, Terrell Mattox, Athens Christian: Kellogg blocked a punt and an extra point in a 51-13 rout of Providence Christian on Friday. Turner scored off a blocked punt. Lee had a rushing and passing touchdown. Mattox also scored. Zeb Noland, Tyler Davis, Oconee County: Noland scored three times in a 29-0 rout of Jackson County on Friday. Davis scored on a 5-yard run. Drew Richardson, Payton Bowles, Athens Academy: Richardson scored two touchdown passes in a 36-7 win against Towns County. Bowles snagged a scoring pass and rushed for a touchdown. Brock Landis, Winder-Barrow: Landis scored off runs of 1 and 25 yards and threw for another touchdown in a 24-17 win over Flowery Branch. Kevon Hudson, Prince Avenue Christian: Hudson scored twice in a 35-14 win against Commerce on Friday. Volleyball Ansley McClain, Maggie Carlson, Emily Boswell, Oconee County: McClain had 29 assists and six aces in sweeps of Hart County and Morgan County last Tuesday. McClain (20 kills, 11 digs), Carlson (48 assists) and Boswell (45 digs) paced the Warriors in a win over Athens Christian and a loss to Athens Academy on Thursday. Olivia Przybysz, Madison Corbett, Abby Wood, Grace Haney, Jefferson: Przybysz (19 digs), Corbett (two aces, 20 assists), Wood (three aces, 19 digs) and Haney (six kills, 22 assists) contributed to Jefferson’s sweeps of Jackson County and East Jackson on Thursday. Emi Melendez, East Jackson: Melendez had 20 kills and 20 blocks as the Eagles split matches against Tallulah Falls and Rabun County on Tuesday. Softball Alexis Berry, Jakayla Sullivan, Mckenzie McFarland, Winder-Barrow: Berry pitched a complete game one-hitter with eight strikeouts and four walks in an 11-0 win against Gainesville on Tuesday. Sullivan had two hits and three RBIs. McFarland had a hit, two runs and three stolen bases. Cross country Thomas Moore, North Oconee: Moore finished first (15:38.60) in the boys race at the Mountain Invitational on Thursday. Chase Kennedy, Sue Ann Morales, East Jackson: Kennedy was second (15:46.00) at the boys race at the Mountain Invitational on Thursday. Morales was second (18:10.80) in the girls race. — Nicole Saavedra/Staff
